page.title: 17WILDLIFE
page.content: Around here you can always find wildlife.Just outside our school we saw 20 Sparrows,10 Blackbirds,2 Crows,1 Robin and 1 Housemartin in just 25 minutes.Along the river and in the river you can find all sorts of wildlife like frogs,toads,voles,rats and many sorts of fish.Class 3P went to the river and found minnows, eels,Canadian pondweed,rushes,gnats, spiders,Mallard ducks,butterflies. Along the banks they found stitchworts lesser celandine,blackthorn,willows, hawthorn.They also saw tracks of Mallard ducks. Dow wood is a very healthy wood with many pheasants and a herd of deer. Deer have been known to wander into people's gardens.{
